{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 220°C. Place butternut squash on a baking tray, drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Roast for 35-40 minutes, until edges are browned. Meanwhile, prepare chilli.","Place coriander in mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 8<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place onions, oil, garlic and chilli in mixing bowl then chop <b>4 sec\/speed 8<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then sauté <b>5 min\/120°C\/speed 1<b>.","Add chilli powder, cumin, chipotle paste, smoked paprika, pepper, tomatoes and stock cube. Mix well with spatula and cook <b>15 min\/100°C\/\/speed <b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then blend <b>15 sec\/speed 8<b>.","Add vinegar and black beans then cook <b>5 min\/100°C\/\/speed <b>.","Stir in roasted butternut squash, add lime juice and season to taste. Serve chilli in bowls garnished with reserved chopped coriander."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["1 butternut squash, (approx. 1100-1200 g), peeled, diced (2.5 cm)","1 Tbsp olive oil","1 tsp fine sea salt","1 tsp ground black pepper","10 g fresh coriander, leaves only","200 g onions, quartered","50 g olive oil","2 garlic cloves","1 fresh red chilli, deseeded, if desired","1 tsp chilli powder","1 tsp ground cumin","1 tsp chipotle paste","1 tsp smoked paprika","1 pinch ground black pepper","400 g tinned chopped tomatoes","1 vegetable stock cube (for 0.5 l), crumbled","2 Tbsp cider vinegar","460 g tinned black beans (approx 2 x 400 g tins, drained)","40 g lime juice"]}],"id":"r177826","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-lwsKnbMEx3w\/XZVRWRj-s0I\/AAAAAAAAdNQ\/TGuoeDcyo_Mr6WOh8flv7YXaLWDhERXEQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_mYvQ1_xwhEOlYTVv.png","title":"Allergen Friendly Roasted Butternut Squash and Black Bean Chilli","publishedAt":"2017-07-17T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"10.2 g","fat":"11.5 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"29 g","calories":"1220 kJ \/ 292 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking tray, oven","hintsAndTricks":["This vegan chilli provides plenty of nutrients and protein and can be served either on its own or with rice or a jacket potato. For a cooling finish to the meal, try making the <i>Vegan Strawberry Ice Cream.<\/i>","Serve topped with chopped avocado, dairy-free cheese or sour cream."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","45m","6 portions"]}